The paper deals with security requirements in distributed software systems, specifically authorization policies, and proposes a model for specifying communication and dynamic authorization handling. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Software Engineering (cs.SE), or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories.
